      "content": "The evidence from twin studies, when interpreted by those who support genetic determinism, is used to argue that some groups are biologically predisposed to higher or lower cognitive function. These researchers often claim that the observed IQ gaps reflect a genuine, fixed hierarchy of intellectual capacity among different racial groups. It is important to note, however, that this interpretation is heavily criticized by the majority of mainstream scientists who argue that \"heritability\" only describes variance *within* a group, not the absolute difference *between* groups.",
